
Locators
----------------------------------



Types of Locators
----------------------------------
- We can identify various elements on the web page using Locators
- Locators are addresses that identity web element uniquely within the page

1) Basic Locators
    -id
    -name
    -LinkText, PartialLinkTest
    -Class name
    -Tag name

2) Customized Locators
    i) CSS Selector
        -Tag and ID
        -Tag and Class
        -Tag and attribute
        -Tag, class and attribute

    ii) XPath
        -Absolute XPath
        -Relative XPath




findElement() ---- return Single WebElement
findElements() ---- return Multiple WebElements

Scenario 1: Locator matching with single web element
findElement(loc) ---> single web element     |      return type is: WebElement
findElements(loc) ---> single web element    |      return type is: List<WebElement>

Scenario 2: Locator matching with multiple web elements
findElement(loc) ---> single web element     |      return type is: WebElement
findElements(loc) ---> multiple web elements    |      return type is: List<WebElement>

Scenario 2: Locator is not matching with any element/s
findElement(loc) ---> its through No Such Element Exception
findElements(loc) ---> will not through any exception but Return 0




